<div class="extra">
<h3>🧐 About the Story</h3>
<p>
“The Third Level” by Jack Finney is a short story blending reality and fantasy. 
It tells the story of Charley, a 31-year-old man who discovers a mysterious third level at Grand Central Station, which seems to belong to the year 1894. 
The story explores human desire to escape the stress of modern life and seek a simpler, peaceful past.
</p>
